title.narrative: BEHAVIOUR CHANGE FOR HEALTH

description.narrative: Targeted communities acquire positive behaviour and demonstrate enhanced demand for health services, with particular focus on the neonatal period., which contributes to Child Health, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Maternal And Newborn Health, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Targeted communities acquire positive behaviour and demonstrate enhanced demand for health services, with particular focus on the neonatal period.

description.narrative: Since the start of the COVID-19, GCO provides support and leadership in the RCCE pillar at the national (NRCCE) and regional (RRCCE) and community levels to streamline social mobilization forincreased awareness and perception of health risk as well as promote uptake of COVID-19 vaccination. In addition, provided support around fulfillment of C4D requirements for introduction of nOPV2 and social mobilization and communication component of the polio vaccination campaign using nOPV2 vaccines.;GCO continue to support government to scale up the 4+4 plus key household practices in North Bank Region (NBR) by working with community-based mechanisms. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/12/2021
